📝 Scenario
You are writing a script for an automated warehouse robot. The robot needs to decide if it can pick up a combined load of electronics and determine if the operation is safe and within budget.

🛠 Part 1: The Variables
Initialize the following variables in your program:

int laptopCount = 10;
int phoneCount = 20;
decimal laptopPrice = 500.50m;
decimal phonePrice = 200.25m;
double laptopWeight = 2.5; // in kg\
double phoneWeight = 0.5; // in kg
decimal budgetLimit = 10000.00m;
double weightLimit = 40.0;

⚙️ Part 2: The Tasks
Task 1: Arithmetic & Precedence
Calculate the Total Value of the inventory and the Total Weight.
Total Value: (Laptops × Price) + (Phones × Price).
Total Weight: (Laptops × Weight) + (Phones × Weight).
Note to students: Pay attention to how the compiler handles the order of multiplication and addition!

Task 2: Assignment Operators
The warehouse charges a flat "Processing Fee" of $150.
Use a compound assignment operator (+=) to add this fee to your previously calculated Total Value.

Task 3: Comparison & Logical Operators
Create a boolean variable named isOperationSafe. This should be true ONLY if:
The Total Value is less than or equal to the budgetLimit.
AND the Total Weight is strictly less than the weightLimit.
*/

using System;
class Program {
    static void Main() {
        int laptopcount = 10;
        int phonecount = 10;
        decimal laptopprice = 500.50m;
        decimal phoneprice = 200.25m;
        double laptopWeight = 2.5;
        double phoneWeight = 0.5;
        decimal budgetLimit = 10000.00m;
        double weightLimit = 40.0;

        decimal totalvalue = (laptopcount * laptopprice) + (phonecount * phoneprice);
        double totalweight = (laptopcount * laptopWeight) + (phonecount * phoneWeight);
        totalvalue += 150;
        

        bool isOperation = (totalvalue <= budgetLimit) && (totalweight < weightLimit);

        if (isOperation) {
            Console.WriteLine("-----Warehouse Report-------");
            Console.WriteLine($"Total Value of order after processing fee : {totalvalue}"); 
            Console.WriteLine($"Total weight of the order : {totalweight}");
        }
        else{
            Console.WriteLine("Operation is out of range either total value is more than the budget limit or total weight is out of range of weight limit");
        }

    }
}
